Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
highlightSyncObj(25.10)                                highlightSyncObj(25.10)

Name
       highlightSyncObj  - Adds highlight color on sync objects during master-
       clone-aware bus guide operations

Syntax
       highlightSyncObj

       [-help]

       [-obj {all busGuides}]

       Adds highlight color on  sync  objects  during  master-clone-aware  bus
       guide operations. The colors used for highlighting are based on differ-
       ent  color schema categories - user-drawn, bounded, or unbounded. These
       categories are derived from the last sync command (clonePtnObj -sync or
       setFPlanMode -autoSyncMasterClone busGuides) used. This  command  makes
       it  easy  to distinguish between different bus guide objects in the de-
       sign.

              * User-drawn bus guides are highlighted in yellow.

              * Bounded bus guides are highlighted in red. Nets in bounded bus
                guides can be determined during sync operation. If either  (or
                both)  the  source  or driver partition is a master-clone, the
                tool can determine the equivalent net during sync  (in  master
                clone chains).

                For  example:  Consider  A1-B1-C1  and  A2-B2-C2  chains where
                A/B/C1 A/B/C2 are master clones. A1/2 pin k  is  connected  to
                net  n1  (in A1) and n2 (in A2). As we can easily determine n1
                and n2 in the chains, this is a case of bounded bus guides.

              * Unbounded bus guides are highlighted  in  blue.  Nets  in  un-
                bounded bus guides cannot be determined during sync operation.
                If both source or driver partition are unique or (special case
                master  and  clone  but their equivalent pin is floating), the
                tool cannot determine the net during sync (in master and clone
                chains).

                For example: Consider UA1-B1-UC1 and UA2-B2-UC2  chains  where
                B1  and  B2  are master clones. UA1/UC1/UA2/UC2 are all unique
                but UA1/UA2 pin may be different. Here since we cannot  deter-
                mine  equivalent  nets  of chains, this is a case of unbounded
                bus guides.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each highlightSyncObj parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man highlightSyncObj

       -obj {all busGuides}
              Specifies the object to be highlighted.

              Data_type: enum_list, optional

Example
              * The  following command highlights busguides based on different
                color schema categories:

                highlightSyncObj -obj busGuides

       Related Information

              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

